"You just killed a man for gold; a fair number of the guild members probably wouldn't like to hear about that."

value.0: "That looked pretty easy, hardly worth 100 gold, but a deal is a deal. Here is your gold, I just hope this doesn't make trouble for your election campaign."
"Why would I ask you to kill one of my oldest and dearest friends? Deus, Mac, did I ask <FirstName> to kill my old friend Typhus?"
"He did? That's not the way I remember it. How about you, Deus? Mac?"
"Typhus just walk in here all nice, then <FirstName> jump him and kill him. That be what me saw."
"It laughs at man then kills him."
"There, you see what kind of trouble you could get into around here? Luckily, I am in a generous mood and am willing to forget that this all happened."
"It would look bad if my accounts came up short though, if you know what I mean."
"I take some offense at your tone, but please, go on. It's not as if I'm going to have you killed or anything, just because you get on my bad side."
"Indeed. Now how about my gold?"
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> Thaddeus sneers at you. "Keep the gold... I was only having a little fun with you."
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> "Keep the gold... I was only having a little fun with you."
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> Thaddeus sneers at you. "Keep the gold... I was only having a little fun with you."
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> "Keep the gold... I was only having a little fun with you."
"I see. Very well then, keep the 100 gold and don't worry about the assassination, I was only having a little... fun with you."
"I mean that if you give me back my 100 gold, I'll forget you assassinated my good friend Typhus! How difficult is that to understand?"
"I think I might be starting to see a pattern here. I'll tell you what, you keep that gold and I'll give you my vote. There is one more little job I need done though."
"There is a woman named Gelani who used to be the master of the merchants' guild. She is a popular lady, part owner of The Mossy Tree and some of her supporters have been causing me grief."
"I think Gelani needs to go away for a while... let us say... for eternity."
"The pay for being <Lord/Lady> of the keep is high indeed, with the potential for all sorts of corruption and vice. Besides, I just paid you 100 gold for a very easy task. Think about it."
"Sir Becket thinks he deserves to rule, which makes him difficult to work with. I like you better. I think we'd have a better relationship, so do this little favor for me and you'll get your vote."

"That is unfortunate to hear. I guess Sir Becket is the better candidate then. Oh, and don't think you can go telling anyone about this little deal. No one will believe you... or those that do won't care."
"Goodbye, for now."
"Indeed! Very well, once Gelani has left our beloved keep for good, and moved on to the realm of Mistress Death, you will get my vote."
"Goodbye, for now."
"This guy's a real professional, <FirstName>. You'd better be careful around him."
"I guess that is your repayment for helping such an obviously twisted criminal. I think you killed the wrong one."
"Oh, he is a nasty, trickster, <FirstName>! I would love to get him into a dark alley and tear out his throat and chew off his ears, I would!"

"He is testing you, <FirstName>. He wants to know how easy you would be to manipulate as the <lord/lady>. Give him what he wants, and he'll think he can control you. It might be an easy way to get a vote."
"You just killed a man for gold; a fair number of the guild members probably wouldn't like to hear about that."

value.0: "I hear Gelani is gone. Here's an extra little something for your trouble. So tell me, <Lord/Lady> <FirstName>, how can Thaddeus help you today?" Thaddeus gives you a leering wink.
"Welcome to The Tarnished Tankard, friend!" With a quick grin and a clap of his hands, this gnome greets you in an expansive manner.
"I am Thaddeus Squilt, sole proprietor of this fine establishment and master of the merchants' guild. And might I know who it is that I am speaking to?"
"Indeed! The very <man/woman> who has challenged my benefactor, Sir Becket. I hope you aren't here to sway my vote, ha, ha. That could be expensive indeed."

Comment.value: spawn in Typhus, he comes over to Thaddeus

value.0: "If you are here about the election, this conversation could get expensive. If you are here for a drink, or just for some local gossip, I would be pleased to assist you."
"Come back and visit anytime. We always like patrons with coin to spend."
"That is the second job of a tavern keeper, local gossip collector, ha. What would you like to know?"
"Are you certain? Would you like a drink before you go?"
"I love most of the people of the keep as my own children, though there are a few exceptions. What do you want to know?"
"Was there anything else you wanted to know about?"
"The army will destroy them. I'm not too worried. Everyone likes to get hysterical about these sort of things, but this is the frontier; we're supposed to expect monster attacks."
"I don't really care where you stay, just don't pass out here, or you'll likely be robbed... by the patrons or the staff, take your pick."
"I would suggest you try the Pawnshop. Southpaw gets some very interesting equipment from his... sources."
"I know Serah, the landowners guild master has been complaining about goblins on her land. She's usually in the Guild Office, in the Guildhall."

"Ha, ha, a good tale that one! Gelani, part owner of The Mossy Tree was the guild master for a while. The problem was, she kept agreeing with the Banner when it came to increasing taxes for the army."
"Now, if there is one thing that merchants and nobles hate, it's paying taxes. One day Sir Becket was in here, as he often is, and we got to talking about the tax rates."
"When he realized that I would help his love, Elyssia, stop the Banner from increasing taxes again, he came up with a plan."
"Very well, though I think it is a terribly clever tale. What else would you like to know about?"
"Wait, I'm not at the best part yet!"

"I began to spread rumors that she was proposing a plan to double taxes! The rumor spread so fast that Gelani was suddenly being tripped and having little accidents in the streets and even in her own tavern."
"Her own partner became upset when it was discovered that Gelani was stealing from their profits, something he discovered too late was completely false."
"By the time she was replaced, Gelani's self-confidence was shattered. She didn't even put up a fight! It was wonderful!"
"It does make the perfect ending to the story, doesn't it? Brings a tear to my eye... ha!"
"That would have made the story better. Still, the story might not be over yet. Anything else?"
"It wouldn't work with the time frame you have; besides, twice so soon would probably backfire. Anything else you would like to know?"
"I know... sheer genius! So what else would you like to know?"
"The Tarnished Tavern welcomes those patrons who aren't welcome in certain other establishments. It means people coming here have a far more interesting time than elsewhere."
"Why, you never know when you be visited by a thief, pummeled in a tavern brawl, or catch some disease from... well, never mind that. It's all in good fun!"
"I am afraid to tell you this, but I will be voting for Sir Becket. He assisted me in getting my position in the guild and he has helped finance me several times."
"Ah, here comes Typhus and it looks like he is very upset. In fact, he rather seems to have the look of someone about to kill me."
"Thaddeus, you backstabbing, little bastard! I am going to cut off your buttocks and feed them to you! You've ruined me!"
"There, there Typhus, calm yourself. You must learn not to be such a sore loser."
"Sore loser? I just lost my family and my livelihood because of your 'help', so now I'm going to help you lose your life!"
"<FirstName>, how would you like to make a few quick and easy credits... and a little respect? All you have to do is take care of this... unfortunate incident."
<StartAction>[Sigh]</Start> "Good help is so hard to find. Deus... Mac... take care of this for me."
"Yes boss."
"So... enough pleasure, back to business."
"Wonderful! Just come back and see me when you're done. Hey, Typhus, meet my new friend. <He/She>'s going to kill you now! Ha, ha, ha!"
"It's gone beyond that now. Even if he leaves, he'll just come back. This needs to be finished here."
"100 gold, for a very simple job."
"Everyone here knows Typhus started it. Guards can't do much about that."
"Deal with my friend Typhus over there and we'll talk..."
"I will be voting for Sir Becket. You don't do favors for me, I don't do favors for you. Now, what else?"
"I am still waiting for word about Gelani. Unless she takes a permanent vacation, I will be voting for Sir Becket. Anything else?"
"I will be voting for you, as agreed. Anything else?"
"Indeed! I will fix one for you immediately. We have several types. Would you like an ale (1 gp), a glass of wine (1gp), some honey mead (5gp), or a Flaming Orc's Breath (10gp)?"
"That is unfortunate. So what else can I do for you?"

value.0: "Foul stuff, but potent! I hope you have the stomach for it. I've seen a lot of people pass out from one of these."
"Some strange old woman was in here once and claimed that the ghosts in the graveyard were hiding treasure. I've never heard of ghosts in the graveyard since her ramblings though. Anything else?"
"This drink wouldn't be so expensive if that hermit was a little better at his job. I'll bet the old fool has some good treasure from back when he was sane. Anything else?"

"I do enjoy a nice glass of wine myself. Say, I've heard that Sir Becket cheats on that noble wench, Ellysia. If a person could get evidence of that, I'll bet it would be valuable information. Anything else?"
"Right, here you go, one ale. Say, I don't know if you heard, but somebody tried to steal The Stan's magic boots the other day. Woo hoo, was that funny. I love it when people are stupid!"
"Anyways, would you like to have another drink?"
"I trust all is going well with the monsters, m'Lord <FirstName>."
